==English==

===Etymology===
Dutch [[Amsterdams pond]], '[[Amsterdam]]' (Dutch port city, in Holland) + [[pond]] 'pound' (weight measure.)

===Noun===
'''[[Amsterdam]] [[pound]]'''

# {{obsolete}} One of many locally defined [[weight measure]]s called pound before the introduction of the [[metric system]], important because of its use in the thriving Dutch matitime commerce, equivalent to 0,4941 [[kilogram]].